# Cloud Storage for Firebase

Cloud Storage for Firebase lets you upload, download, and manage user-generated files — images, videos, documents — stored in Google Cloud Storage buckets with Firebase security rules and a global CDN.

## Initialize Storage

```typescript
import { initializeApp } from 'firebase/app';
import { getStorage } from 'firebase/storage';

const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);
const storage = getStorage(app);

// Use a custom bucket
const customStorage = getStorage(app, 'gs://my-custom-bucket');
```

## Create a Storage Reference

References point to files or directories in the bucket. They do not create the file — they are pointers used for operations.

```typescript
import { ref } from 'firebase/storage';

// Reference to a file
const photoRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');

// Reference to a directory
const imagesRef = ref(storage, 'images/');

// Navigate with child, parent, root
const childRef = ref(imagesRef, 'photo.jpg');       // images/photo.jpg
const parentRef = photoRef.parent;                    // images/
const rootRef = photoRef.root;                        // bucket root

// Properties
console.log(photoRef.fullPath);  // 'images/photo.jpg'
console.log(photoRef.name);      // 'photo.jpg'
console.log(photoRef.bucket);    // 'my-project.appspot.com'
```

## Upload a File

### Upload bytes (small files)

```typescript
import { ref, uploadBytes } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');

// From a File object (browser)
const snapshot = await uploadBytes(storageRef, file);
console.log('Uploaded', snapshot.metadata.size, 'bytes');

// From a Uint8Array (Node.js)
const data = new Uint8Array(fs.readFileSync('./photo.jpg'));
const snapshot = await uploadBytes(storageRef, data);
```

### Resumable upload (large files with progress)

```typescript
import { ref, uploadBytesResumable, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'videos/clip.mp4');
const uploadTask = uploadBytesResumable(storageRef, file);

uploadTask.on('state_changed',
  (snapshot) => {
    const progress = (snapshot.bytesTransferred / snapshot.totalBytes) * 100;
    console.log(`Upload: ${progress.toFixed(1)}%`);

    switch (snapshot.state) {
      case 'paused':  console.log('Upload paused'); break;
      case 'running': console.log('Upload running'); break;
    }
  },
  (error) => {
    switch (error.code) {
      case 'storage/unauthorized': console.error('Permission denied'); break;
      case 'storage/canceled':     console.error('Upload canceled'); break;
      case 'storage/quota-exceeded': console.error('Quota exceeded'); break;
      default: console.error('Upload error:', error.message);
    }
  },
  async () => {
    const url = await getDownloadURL(uploadTask.snapshot.ref);
    console.log('Download URL:', url);
  }
);

// Pause, resume, cancel
uploadTask.pause();
uploadTask.resume();
uploadTask.cancel();
```

### Upload a string

```typescript
import { ref, uploadString } from 'firebase/storage';

// Base64
await uploadString(storageRef, base64String, 'base64');

// Base64 URL
await uploadString(storageRef, base64UrlString, 'base64url');

// Data URL (includes content type)
await uploadString(storageRef, dataUrl, 'data_url');

// Raw string
await uploadString(storageRef, 'Hello, World!');
```

## Get Download URL

```typescript
import { ref, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');
const url = await getDownloadURL(storageRef);
// https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/bucket/o/images%2Fphoto.jpg?alt=media&token=...
```

The URL includes an access token and remains valid until the token is revoked in the Firebase console or through the Admin SDK.

## Download Data

```typescript
import { ref, getBytes, getBlob, getStream } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');

// Download into memory (max 256MB default)
const bytes = await getBytes(storageRef);
const data = new Uint8Array(bytes);

// Download as Blob (browser)
const blob = await getBlob(storageRef);
const objectUrl = URL.createObjectURL(blob);

// Download with max size (in bytes)
const bytes = await getBytes(storageRef, 10 * 1024 * 1024); // 10MB max
```

## File Metadata

```typescript
import { ref, getMetadata, updateMetadata } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');

// Get metadata
const metadata = await getMetadata(storageRef);
console.log('Content-Type:', metadata.contentType);
console.log('Size:', metadata.size);
console.log('Created:', metadata.timeCreated);
console.log('Updated:', metadata.updated);
console.log('Custom:', metadata.customMetadata);

// Update metadata
await updateMetadata(storageRef, {
  contentType: 'image/jpeg',
  cacheControl: 'public, max-age=31536000',
  customMetadata: {
    uploadedBy: 'user123',
    originalName: 'vacation-photo.jpg',
  },
});

// Delete a metadata property by setting it to null
await updateMetadata(storageRef, {
  customMetadata: { uploadedBy: null },
});
```

## Delete a File

```typescript
import { ref, deleteObject } from 'firebase/storage';

const storageRef = ref(storage, 'images/photo.jpg');
await deleteObject(storageRef);
```

## List Files

```typescript
import { ref, listAll, list } from 'firebase/storage';

// List everything under a path
const imagesRef = ref(storage, 'images/');
const result = await listAll(imagesRef);

result.items.forEach((itemRef) => {
  console.log('File:', itemRef.fullPath);
});
result.prefixes.forEach((prefix) => {
  console.log('Folder:', prefix.fullPath);
});

// Paginate results
const firstPage = await list(ref(storage, 'images/'), { maxResults: 10 });
if (firstPage.nextPageToken) {
  const secondPage = await list(ref(storage, 'images/'), {
    maxResults: 10,
    pageToken: firstPage.nextPageToken,
  });
}
```

## Security Rules

Security rules live in `storage.rules` and control client SDK access:

```
rules_version = '2';
service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {

    // Authenticated users can read all files
    match /{allPaths=**} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
    }

    // Users can write to their own directory
    match /users/{userId}/{allPaths=**} {
      allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // Restrict upload size and content type
    match /images/{imageId} {
      allow write: if request.auth != null
                   && request.resource.size < 5 * 1024 * 1024
                   && request.resource.contentType.matches('image/.*');
    }

    // Admin-only via custom claims
    match /admin/{allPaths=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth.token.admin == true;
    }
  }
}
```

## CORS Configuration

Required for browser downloads from custom domains. Create a `cors.json`:

```json
[
  {
    "origin": ["https://my-app.web.app", "http://localhost:3000"],
    "method": ["GET", "HEAD", "PUT", "POST", "DELETE"],
    "maxAgeSeconds": 3600
  }
]
```

Apply with gsutil:
```bash
gsutil cors set cors.json gs://my-project.appspot.com
```

## Admin SDK (Server-Side)

The Admin SDK bypasses security rules and accesses the underlying GCS bucket:

```typescript
import { initializeApp, cert } from 'firebase-admin/app';
import { getStorage } from 'firebase-admin/storage';

const app = initializeApp({
  credential: cert(require('./service-account.json')),
  storageBucket: 'my-project.appspot.com',
});

const bucket = getStorage().bucket();

// Upload
await bucket.upload('./local-file.jpg', {
  destination: 'images/photo.jpg',
  metadata: { contentType: 'image/jpeg' },
});

// Download
await bucket.file('images/photo.jpg').download({
  destination: './downloaded.jpg',
});

// Get signed URL (time-limited)
const [url] = await bucket.file('images/photo.jpg').getSignedUrl({
  action: 'read',
  expires: Date.now() + 3600 * 1000,
});

// Delete
await bucket.file('images/photo.jpg').delete();

// List
const [files] = await bucket.getFiles({ prefix: 'images/' });
files.forEach((file) => console.log(file.name));
```
